SOVIET TEAM TO HIT GRIDIRON IN U.S. 
Former Denver Broncos Coach John Ralston will coach a Soviet team that will 
play five American-style football games in the United States in July. 
The tour was announced by the International Sports Connection, which represents 
the USSR-American Football Union, a league made up of 24 teams in the Soviet 
Union. The Moscow Bears will play Minor League Football System teams in Tacoma, 
Wash.; Fresno, Calif.; Oklahoma City; Macon, Ga., and Charlotte, N.C. 
